-- Saints’ Colston Agrees to $40 Million Contract, Picayune Reports
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-03-13T17:27:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/saints-wide-receiver-colston-agrees-to-40-million-contract-picayune-says.html
Wide receiver Marques Colston has
agreed to a five-year contract with the  New Orleans  Saints worth
as much as $40 million, the  Times-Picayune reported , citing an
unidentified National Football League official.  Colston, 28, has had more than 1,000 receiving yards in
five of his six seasons with the Saints. He would have become a
free agent at the start of the new league year later today.  Colston had 80 catches for 1,143 yards and eight touchdowns
over 14 games last season. Colston’s contract is worth between
$35 million and $40 million, and includes between $18 million
and $19 million in guaranteed money, according to the Times-
Picayune of New Orleans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
